  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A Requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis predictions; however, the supporting validation activity relied exclusively on a literature-review of published hemolysis correlations, which the assessment narrative characterises as a complementary evidence synthesis consistent with experimental benchmarks. The structured activityType field records literature-review, breaking the inference link required by the Requirement node.",
