    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concluded that the CFD hemolysis predictions are adequately supported by the literature-review activity, which demonstrated agreement within ±18% of published power-law correlations across all five operating conditions. The team considered this evidence sufficient in combination with the Monte Carlo UQ results. Multiple credibility factors remain below required levels, but the overall evidence package was judged acceptable for the intended regulatory submission. No experimental-validation activity was conducted; the supporting evidence derives solely from the literature-review of published hemolysis correlations.",
